# Data Access Patterns

## Data Fetching — Server Components Only

All data retrieval must be done in Server Components. Never fetch data in Client Components or via API routes for reads.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — data fetched in a Server Component
export default async function DecksPage() {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
  return <DeckList decks={userDecks} />;
}

// ❌ BAD — fetching in a Client Component
"use client";
export function DecksPage() {
  const [decks, setDecks] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => { fetch("/api/decks").then(...) }, []);
}
```

## Mutations — Server Actions Only

All inserts, updates, and deletes must be performed via Server Actions — never via Route Handlers or client-side fetch calls.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — server action
"use server";
export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) { ... }

// ❌ BAD — route handler mutation
export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const body = await req.json();
  await db.insert(decks).values(body);
}
```

## Validation — Zod Required

All data passed into Server Actions must be validated with Zod. Define a Zod schema, infer the TypeScript type from it, and use that type as the parameter — never use `FormData` as a parameter type.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
import { z } from "zod";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(100),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error("Invalid input");
  // proceed with parsed.data
}

// ❌ BAD — no validation, FormData type
export async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get("title");
  await db.insert(decks).values({ title });
}
```
